From: Alcatraz vendor patches <noreply@alcatraz.local>
Subject: [PATCH 1/1] overlay: ensure parent dirs in delta before Mkdir

OverlayFS.Mkdir and MkdirAll call delta.Mkdir(p) directly. When the
parent of p exists only in the base layer (not yet copied into the
delta), delta.Mkdir returns ENOENT. The fix is to run ensureParentDirs
(which materialises the missing parents in the delta via copy-up) before
each delta.Mkdir, and to recurse MkdirAll through OverlayFS.Mkdir so the
copy-up runs at every component.

This is required for the alcatraz.worker spawn pipeline, which uses
OverlayHandle.WriteFile to plant /etc/ssh/auth_principals/al and
/etc/ssh/trusted_user_ca_keys into the per-sandbox overlay before VM
boot. Without it, mkdir of /etc/ssh/auth_principals fails because
/etc/ssh exists only in the base rootfs.

Tracks upstream tursodatabase/agentfs at tag v0.6.4 (commit 3a5ed2b).
Originally from a working-tree edit on the alcatraz developer's local
agentfs checkout; not yet upstreamed.

---
diff --git a/sdk/go/overlay.go b/sdk/go/overlay.go
index b662566..9b13c19 100644
--- a/sdk/go/overlay.go
+++ b/sdk/go/overlay.go
@@ -1044,6 +1044,13 @@ func (ofs *OverlayFS) Mkdir(ctx context.Context, p string, mode int64) error {
 	// Invalidate cache before creating directory
 	ofs.invalidateCache(p)

+	// Ensure parent directories are materialized in delta (copy-up from base).
+	// Without this, delta.Mkdir fails with ENOENT on the parent path when the
+	// parent only exists in the base layer.
+	if err := ofs.ensureParentDirs(ctx, p, 0, 0); err != nil {
+		return err
+	}
+
 	return ofs.delta.Mkdir(ctx, p, mode)
 }

@@ -1070,10 +1077,9 @@ func (ofs *OverlayFS) MkdirAll(ctx context.Context, p string, mode int64) error
 			if !IsNotExist(err) {
 				return err
 			}
-			// Invalidate cache before creating
-			ofs.invalidateCache(currentPath)
-			// Create in delta
-			if err := ofs.delta.Mkdir(ctx, currentPath, mode); err != nil {
+			// Use overlay-aware Mkdir so parent dirs get copied up from base
+			// when needed (delta.Mkdir alone fails if the parent lives only in base).
+			if err := ofs.Mkdir(ctx, currentPath, mode); err != nil {
 				return err
 			}
 		} else if !stats.IsDir() {
--
